Christine Head, STEM teacher at Oak Ridge Intermediate, has been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. Christine is a Camdenton graduate who demonstrates a tremendous work ethic, character, and Laker Pride in her teaching practices. Christine also is a lead communicator to our community through her oversight of our school’s Facebook page. Her contributions in both the classroom and beyond make her a valuable commodity and the District is proud to call her ours. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

To view past recipients: https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

Malinda Beushausen, Cassidy Dickerson, Vicki Luber, Meghan Steveson, Shannon Stoufer, Shayla Viele, and Jody Watson, District Instructional Coaching team, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. This team got us off to a great start by training our new teachers in the “Camdenton Way” of instructional strategies and technology usage. They then worked with the curriculum teams to build a foundation that allowed our teachers to start the year off on the right foot. Furthermore, this team worked tirelessly this summer to prepare our teachers for seated instruction and distance learning. The district is proud of their hard work and dedication. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

To view past recipients: https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

post_text: Tuscany Condominiums, Camdenton, MO, came together over the Labor Day weekend in support of the Camdenton School District Buddy Pack program. Owners donated food items as well as made monetary donations exceeding $1100.00! The Buddy Packs provide identified children with bags of kid-friendly nutrition to assure they have enough to eat on weekends and over holidays. Representing the Tuscany Condo family, pictured left to right: Jerry and Sandy Andel, Joi Dickemann, Larry and Carol Byars, and Barb and Tim Schwane. More information about the Buddy Pack program can be found at www.sharefoodbringhope.org or contact Joi Dickemann at the Camdenton School District (573) 346-9243.

post_text:
LCTC Students Recognized as Important Heroes

“I fear that our community is not recognizing our most important heroes. I have watched these young people show their strength in clinicals during trying times and they returned to start a new day. We have entered an era that demands strength of character, compassion, the willingness to learn, reliability during their tasks, their commitment to care for my residents, and the love for their community in following critical steps to protect others from this deadly virus. I want to thank these young men and women for being there when we needed them. They return to their jobs despite the fears of the unknown. My residents and our staff appreciate every step they take in this facility and their display of honor and love for our residents. Please let each and every one of these students know that they are our unsung heroes that are our future caretakers and that they are recognized by us. We love them all."

"Thank you so much for being a part of our lives,”
Sharon Konwinski and Staff
Camdenton Windsor Estates

Lake Career and Technical Center
May 29 at 10:00 AM ·

The goal of NTHS is to recognize deserving technical students so that people of the community become aware of the talents and abilities of the young people who choose technical education pathways. The seven attributes of NTHS membership are skill, honesty, service, responsibility, scholarship, citizenship, and leadership. A group of 19 seniors at LCTC qualified and have been selected for the honor of being members of the National Technical Honor Society. These students are receiving certificates of membership and purple and silver cords to wear at graduation. Congratulations!!! #LCTCCelebrates

Amy Atler, Kyla Kirtley, and Warren Roth, Camdenton Middle School eighth-grade English-Language Art's team educators, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. This team creates lessons that are engaging and intentionally planned to support distance learning. They have offered students a choice board as an effective way to build student engagement. The choices then allow students to explore a wide variety of genres. The layout of the choice board provides students with clear expectations and an understanding of what success looks like. This team has also done a great job of supporting our non-internet students during this time of at-home learning. Camdenton School District appreciates the hard work of the eighth-grade English-Language Art's team. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.
To view past recipients: https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

post_text:
Brittani Holladay, Rebecca Lane, and Andrea Weiss, kindergarten math content team teachers, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. This group of teachers is a true team, each one using their strengths to help the others. They are a well-organized and energized team ready to teach their students engaging and hands-on math lessons at home. This dedicated team of teachers has chosen to meet more often than planned to make sure that everything is perfect for the upcoming week’s lessons. They have each taken time to learn new skills with technology and really deliver personal lessons to our youngest learners. Camdenton School District is proud that this team is leading the young Lakers! Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

For past teacher of the week recipients:
https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

May 18 at 9:04 AM · Camdenton, MO ·

The Camdenton Middle School Science Research team educators, Amy Larrington and Tim Mulford, are pleased to announce that nine Camdenton Middle School Science Research students competed at the Ozarks Science and Engineering Fair (held virtually this year from the Missouri State University campus) between April 28 and May 12. Despite the ongoing uncertainty with COVID-19 all of the Camdenton Middle School students excelled! “We are so proud of all our Science Research students and their accomplishments,” state Larrington and Mulford.

Tyler Dinsdale, Cassidy Palan, and Par Pitts, the Middle School seventh-grade social studies team, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. This team has worked really hard this year to develop new unit plans that better align to standards and to social science inquiry. Recently, they have found unique and standards-based ways to connect virtually with their students. They are focusing each week on a specific culture and even including a cooking show! This has been the perfect way to engage students and parents working together at home. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

To view past recipients: https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

In addition to celebrating the success of the students who attend LCTC, we want to take this opportunity to also recognize faculty members for their achievements. Each year teachers are selected at the building level to be a candidate for Teacher of the Year and Educator of the Year. #LCTCCelebrates

LCTC’s Educator of the Year is Mr. Jeff Kitchen. Mr. Kitchen is one of the Agriculture program instructors at LCTC. He was selected by administration as the LCTC Educator of the Year. We appreciate all you do for our students, Mr. Kitchen!

Mr. Ryan Bearden is LCTC’s Teacher of the Year. Mr. Bearden is the Construction program instructor at LCTC and was selected by his peers for this recognition. Thank you for your dedication and service to our students, Mr. Bearden!

May 1, 2020
Brittany Hill, Jody Hilton, and Jessica Perryman, fifth grade social studies team, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. During this unprecedented time, teaching social studies is as important now as it ever has been. Together they have put an incredible amount of thought and planning into developing and presenting kid-friendly and engaging social studies assignments for their fifth grader students during this time of distance learning. Camdenton School District appreciates the effort and time put in by this fifth grade team. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.
To view past recipients: https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

post_text:
Felicia Boyster, Hannah Lipps, and Carol Patrick, district second grade reading team, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. These teachers have collaborated from buildings across our district to provide meaningful and engaging lessons to our second grade students. By using technological tools, these teachers are working to ensure that our current second grader students will be as ready as the can be for third grade in the fall. Further, Hannah made an instructional video on how to use Loom to share with all teachers. This has made virtual teaching a bit more manageable. Camdenton School District appreciates the amazing efforts and collaborative nature of these amazing teachers! Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

To view past recipients: https://www.camdentonschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1005513&type=d&pREC_ID=1270738

post_text: Ms. Bonds, LCTC Health Science instructor, volunteered several weeks ago to deliver food to our students on the Wednesday food delivery buses. Ms. Bonds posted the "awesomeness" of what our district is doing on her personal Facebook page. A friend and Camdenton 1987 alumni, Pauline Coleman-Carnley, saw her post and volunteered to make masks for the volunteers. Ms. Bonds dropped the masks off yesterday, and they were delivered to Mr. Cuendet this morning to distribute to today's volunteers. Ms. Bonds shared, "Pauline is hoping that anyone who may need help, will reach out to her." It's a Great Day to be a Laker!

Judi Amerine, Malinda Beushausen, Tracy Evans, Cheryl Hymes, Dee Klein, Vicki Luber, Shannon Stoufer, Shayla Viele, and Jody Watson, district instructional coaches, have been named Camdenton School District Teachers of the Week. The global pandemic created by the COVID 19 virus has forced schools to become proficient in distance learning. The district instructional coaches have been the leaders in orchestrating our current system for learning by providing curricular and emotional support to our teachers. Their positive, can-do attitudes have been a tremendous help to district teachers during this time. Further, the instructional coaches have been able to keep the district's curriculum on track so that teachers can focus on teaching. Their value has been immeasurable during this unprecedented time. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

post_text: Bringing the community together - that’s our Walmart friends. Last quarter, your Camdenton Walmart employees met their goal and when the goal is met, they typically have a celebration. In these tough times, with social distancing, this could not happen. Pictured is your Camdenton Walmart manager Paul Gardner and along with associate Josh Breedlove representing each Walmart employee. These hard working members of our community decided to donate $500.00, which would normally celebrate their achievement, to the Camdenton District’s Buddy Pack program. When you see these Walmart associates in the store, please thank them for helping our kids receive a buddy pack during this very difficult time. Thank you Walmart!

shared_text:
Hawthorn Elementary - Camdenton is at Dogwood Animal Shelter.
March 11 at 12:43 PM · Osage Beach, MO ·

As part Hawthorn Elementary students leadership roles, the Kindness Team conducted a fundraising campaign for the Dogwood Animal Shelter. On President’s day we had a snow makeup day, so the team decided to host a PJs and President’s Day event. Students brought in Presidents (coins) to donate and also were able to wear PJ’s for the day. When the donations were all tallied, the students and staff had raised $217.17. Pictured is the Kindness Team presenting the check to Lisa Burns, representative from the Dogwood Animal Shelter. Hawthorn Elementary third grade teachers Angela Stolte and Stefanie Wirths sponsor this leadership team.

post_text:
Faithbridge Church in Osage Beach packed boxes of food to deliver to area schools and organizations on Sunday, March 8. There were over 80 volunteers helping in this endeavor. Through generous donations, Faithbridge Church purchased all items locally at a reduced price through Hy-Vee. The food, hygiene products, and paper goods totaled over 7,000 items, which equaled over 10,000 lbs. of food and supplies! The Camdenton R-III School District received a plethora of boxes to hand out to families and homeless students in our district. Faith Bridge Church was able to send these much needed boxes to eight different organizations helping approximately 400 families.
Pictured: Assistant Maintenance Director Scott Martin along with Faithbridge Church volunteer Larry Basta

shared_text:
Camdenton High School
March 9 at 2:09 PM ·

The Camdenton Speech and Debate team regained the MSHSAA South-Central District title. The tournament was held at West Plains High School on March 6-7, 2020. Twenty-one schools competed in the district tournament. Camdenton took first overall Sweepstakes, 1st Debate Sweepstakes, and 2nd Speech Sweepstakes. This was the 13th time since 1998 that Camdenton has claimed the District title!

Individual Results were:
Jacob Curley-1st, United States Extemporaneous Speaking-State Qualifier
Tommy Garagnani and Aiden Risner-1st Policy Debate-State Qualifier
Maile Huffman-1st Dramatic Interpretation-State Qualifier
Aiden Risner-2nd Foreign Extemporaneous Speaking-State Qualifier
Dylan Frey and Joshua Curley-2nd Policy Debate
Jacob Curley and Simon Miller-3rd Public Forum Debate
Lexi Jones-3rd Lincoln-Douglas Debate
Lexi-Jones-4th Storytelling
Lexi Jones-5th Original Oratory
Jacob Curley-5th Radio Speaking

Dogwood is blessed to have her as part of their team. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.

Ariana Delgado and Jonah Wilkerson students in Medical Detectives class work through a program on their computer to diagnose a medical problem. Payten Luaders: Novice Student Congress

post_text:
Camdenton R-III School District School Board Vice-President Nancy Masterson recently attended the National School Board Association (NSBA) Advocacy institute in Washington, D.C., which also included an additional day at the NSBA Education Equity symposium. Although time was scheduled to visit with our congressional delegation, other activities in the capitol cancelled those face-to-face visits at this time.

Information and ideas obtained during the time spent in Washington can be brought back to our district to help make informed decisions in the future and learn about and consider new opportunities for our students. Talking with other school board members from across the United States is a way to gauge whether we are ahead or lagging behind in what we offer our students. In almost all instances, we can be very proud of the educational opportunities and choices available to our students in the Camdenton R-III School District.

January 31, 2020
Stefanie Wirths, third grade teacher at Hawthorn Elementary, has been named Camdenton School District Teacher of the Week. Stefanie has been an amazing addition to the Hawthorn family. After teaching the majority of her career in second grade, Mrs. Wirths made the decision to transition to Hawthorn and teach third grade. Hawthorn has benefited tremendously as she has jumped in with both feet. She has been a positive contributor to her grade level team. She invests time and energy into delivering quality, engaging lessons, and constantly looks for ways to not only support her students, but her fellow colleagues as well. Teacher of the Week is sponsored by Smith Law Firm and recognizes teachers for positive contributions made to the Camdenton students and district.
